
I heard the story of a woman who was raped in the woods. On that trip there were more than 120 people and all were caught along the way by the bandits, two in front of them with rifles and two in the back, and they started checking them all to take away their belongings. The men were beaten and the women had their fingers in their vaginas or raped. However, this group was able to reach Honduras, but the woman they had raped was separated from the group, had no mercy on her and returned her to Costa Rica. This young woman was so ashamed that she said that nothing had been done to her; but an acquaintance of hers who had seen it all, narrated it,

No one could be trusted, for many lies were told here to make money or to survive. The same dealers when we entered the jungle immediately ambushed us, because they were already well organized. This was one of the reasons people wanted to travel by sea. The problem is, there was no protection there and you could drown. Many of us didn't know how to swim,


