It was categorical the misery on the border between Costa Rica and Nicaragua, there were no authorities waiting for us, no one offered us anything. On this border the one who has money, has to eat
On one occasion, one of the boats did not'll'egó to port, was lost at the bottom of the sea with several migrants. And there was another case of a baby falling into the water and unfortunately the ship's captain wouldn't stop. Everyone was angry and desperate, but -- even though people wanted to help -- it wasn't possible to do it. The ship had to run its course. When people would fall off their backpacks or their bags, they would have less to stop,

Another way to travel was by land inside a trailer that passed through customs. The drivers did it when they found an acquaintance of them working at customs. It was a way to get to Honduras faster. Every night there were people waiting for some driver to help them continue. Sometimes they did, but the same way there were traps, for the thieves were lurking,

